{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779254734277,"sessionID":"ses_1bc27ca67ffe7twbk28GWfzUrI","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_9GgJSMCecsm4mnJhGHXZ6676","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/skills/dev/ensure-servers/SKILL.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/skills/dev/ensure-servers/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Ensures dev servers (backend + frontend) are running on the correct ports with health verification. Kills only this project's stale processes (via PM2 PREFIX), auto-resolves port collisions, and starts fresh. Supports multiple projects running simultaneously.\n3: ---\n4: \n5: # Ensure Servers Skill\n6: \n7: Deterministic server startup protocol. Reads ports and PM2 prefix from project config, auto-resolves port collisions with other projects, kills only this project's stale processes, starts servers via PM2, and health-checks before returning.\n8: \n9: **Purpose**: Eliminate the class of bugs where QA/tests fail because servers aren't running, are on wrong ports, or another project occupies the port.\n10: \n11: **Multi-project safe**: Uses PM2 PREFIX from `ecosystem.config.js` to only manage this project's processes. If preferred ports are occupied by another project, auto-resolves to free ports.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## When to Use\n16: \n17: Call this skill BEFORE any phase that needs running servers:\n18: - Phase 8 (test-api) — smoke tests, backend API tests\n19: - Phase 9 (test-browser) — all sub-phases\n20: - `fullstack --phase test-browser` — smoke, acceptance\n21: - Smoke test skill — needs both servers\n22: - Any manual testing\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## Protocol\n27: \n28: ### Step 1: Read Port Configuration + PM2 Prefix\n29: \n30: Read `ecosystem.config.js` in the project root to get the canonical ports and prefix:\n31: \n32: ```bash\n33: node -e \"\n34: const config = require('./ecosystem.config.js');\n35: const apps = config.apps || [];\n36: apps.forEach(app => {\n37:   const port = app.env?.PORT || (app.args?.match(/--port\\s+(\\d+)/)?.[1]);\n38:   console.log(app.name + ':' + (port || 'default'));\n39: });\n40: \"\n41: ```\n42: \n43: Expected output (tirebank uses prefix `tb`):\n44: ```\n45: tb-backend:3003\n46: tb-frontend:5175\n47: ```\n48: \n49: Extract:\n50: - `PREFIX`: the common prefix before `-backend` / `-frontend` (e.g., `tb`)\n51: - `BACKEND_PORT`: port for the backend service\n52: - `FRONTEND_PORT`: port for the frontend service\n53: \n54: If `ecosystem.config.js` doesn't exist, fall back to:\n55: - Backend: read `backend/.env` for `PORT=` line, default to `3000`\n56: - Frontend: default to `5173`\n57: - PREFIX: use project folder name\n58: \n59: ### Step 2: Verify Frontend .env Matches Backend Port\n60: \n61: ```bash\n62: # Read frontend API base URL\n63: cat frontend/.env.local 2>/dev/null || cat frontend/.env 2>/dev/null\n64: ```\n65: \n66: Check that `VITE_API_BASE_URL` uses the same port as `BACKEND_PORT`.\n67: \n68: **If mismatched**: Fix `frontend/.env.local` to use the correct backend port:\n69: ```\n70: VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:{BACKEND_PORT}/api\n71: ```\n72: \n73: This is the #1 cause of \"everything compiles but nothing works\" failures.\n74: \n75: ### Step 3: Check for Port Collisions\n76: \n77: Before killing anything, check if a **different project** already owns the port.\n78: \n79: Define helper function:\n80: ```bash\n81: find_free_port() {\n82:   local port=$1\n83:   while lsof -ti:$port >/dev/null 2>&1; do\n84:     port=$((port + 1))\n85:   done\n86:   echo $port\n87: }\n88: ```\n89: \n90: Check each port:\n91: ```bash\n92: BACKEND_PID=$(lsof -ti:${BACKEND_PORT} 2>/dev/null)\n93: FRONTEND_PID=$(lsof -ti:${FRONTEND_PORT} 2>/dev/null)\n94: \n95: # If port is occupied, check if it's OUR process or another project's\n96: if [ -n \"$BACKEND_PID\" ]; then\n97:   # Look up PM2 process name for this PID\n98:   PM2_NAME=$(pm2 jlist 2>/dev/null | node -e \"\n99:     let d='';process.stdin.on('data',c=>d+=c);process.stdin.on('end',()=>{\n100:       try{JSON.parse(d).forEach(p=>{\n101:         if(p.pid==${BACKEND_PID})console.log(p.name)\n102:       })}catch(e){}\n103:     })\" 2>/dev/null)\n104:   if [ -n \"$PM2_NAME\" ] && ! echo \"$PM2_NAME\" | grep -q \"^${PREFIX}-\"; then\n105:     echo \"WARNING: Port ${BACKEND_PORT} is used by another project ($PM2_NAME)\"\n106:     BACKEND_PORT=$(find_free_port $((BACKEND_PORT + 1)))\n107:     echo \"Resolved to port ${BACKEND_PORT}\"\n108:   fi\n109: fi\n110: \n111: if [ -n \"$FRONTEND_PID\" ]; then\n112:   PM2_NAME=$(pm2 jlist 2>/dev/null | node -e \"\n113:     let d='';process.stdin.on('data',c=>d+=c);process.stdin.on('end',()=>{\n114:       try{JSON.parse(d).forEach(p=>{\n115:         if(p.pid==${FRONTEND_PID})console.log(p.name)\n116:       })}catch(e){}\n117:     })\" 2>/dev/null)\n118:   if [ -n \"$PM2_NAME\" ] && ! echo \"$PM2_NAME\" | grep -q \"^${PREFIX}-\"; then\n119:     echo \"WARNING: Port ${FRONTEND_PORT} is used by another project ($PM2_NAME)\"\n120:     FRONTEND_PORT=$(find_free_port $((FRONTEND_PORT + 1)))\n121:     echo \"Resolved to port ${FRONTEND_PORT}\"\n122:   fi\n123: fi\n124: ```\n125: \n126: ### Step 4: Kill Only This Project's Stale Processes\n127: \n128: **IMPORTANT**: Do NOT use `pm2 delete all` — that kills other projects' servers too.\n129: \n130: ```bash\n131: # Stop only this project's PM2 processes (by prefix)\n132: pm2 delete ${PREFIX}-backend 2>/dev/null || true\n133: pm2 delete ${PREFIX}-frontend 2>/dev/null || true\n134: # Delete any other prefixed processes (dashboards, etc.)\n135: pm2 list 2>/dev/null | grep \"${PREFIX}-\" | awk '{print $4}' | xargs -I{} pm2 delete {} 2>/dev/null || true\n136: \n137: # Kill anything on our FINAL resolved ports (only if not owned by another project)\n138: lsof -ti:${BACKEND_PORT} | xargs kill -9 2>/dev/null || true\n139: lsof -ti:${FRONTEND_PORT} | xargs kill -9 2>/dev/null || true\n140: \n141: # Wait for ports to free up\n142: sleep 1\n143: \n144: # Verify ports are free\n145: lsof -ti:${BACKEND_PORT} && echo \"ERROR: Port ${BACKEND_PORT} still occupied\" && exit 1\n146: lsof -ti:${FRONTEND_PORT} && echo \"ERROR: Port ${FRONTEND_PORT} still occupied\" && exit 1\n147: ```\n148: \n149: ### Step 5: Update Config If Ports Changed\n150: \n151: If Step 3 resolved to different ports than the defaults in `ecosystem.config.js`:\n152: \n153: 1. Update `frontend/.env.local` — set `VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:${BACKEND_PORT}/api`\n154: 2. Update `backend/.env` — set `PORT=${BACKEND_PORT}`\n155: 3. Log the resolved ports clearly so downstream skills use the right values\n156: \n157: ### Step 6: Start Servers\n158: \n159: If ports match `ecosystem.config.js` defaults:\n160: ```bash\n161: pm2 start ecosystem.config.js\n162: ```\n163: \n164: If ports were changed by collision detection, start with explicit overrides:\n165: ```bash\n166: # Backend with port override\n167: cd backend && PORT=${BACKEND_PORT} pm2 start npm --name \"${PREFIX}-backend\" -- run start:dev\n168: \n169: # Frontend with port override\n170: cd frontend && pm2 start npm --name \"${PREFIX}-frontend\" -- run dev -- --port ${FRONTEND_PORT}\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ```bash\n174: # Wait for startup\n175: sleep 5\n176: \n177: # Check PM2 status (shows all projects' processes)\n178: pm2 list\n179: ```\n180: \n181: If PM2 is not available, start manually:\n182: ```bash\n183: cd backend && PORT=${BACKEND_PORT} npm run start:dev &\n184: cd frontend && npm run dev -- --port ${FRONTEND_PORT} &\n185: sleep 8\n186: ```\n187: \n188: ### Step 7: Health Check\n189: \n190: ```bash\n191: # Backend health check (try up to 5 times with 3s intervals)\n192: for i in {1..5}; do\n193:   STATUS=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:${BACKEND_PORT}/api 2>/dev/null)\n194:   if [ \"$STATUS\" = \"200\" ] || [ \"$STATUS\" = \"404\" ]; then\n195:     echo \"Backend healthy on port ${BACKEND_PORT}\"\n196:     break\n197:   fi\n198:   echo \"Backend not ready (attempt $i/5)...\"\n199:   sleep 3\n200: done\n201: \n202: # Frontend health check\n203: for i in {1..5}; do\n204:   STATUS=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:${FRONTEND_PORT} 2>/dev/null)\n205:   if [ \"$STATUS\" = \"200\" ]; then\n206:     echo \"Frontend healthy on port ${FRONTEND_PORT}\"\n207:     break\n208:   fi\n209:   echo \"Frontend not ready (attempt $i/5)...\"\n210:   sleep 3\n211: done\n212: ```\n213: \n214: ### Step 8: Final Verification\n215: \n216: ```bash\n217: BACKEND_OK=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:${BACKEND_PORT}/api)\n218: FRONTEND_OK=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:${FRONTEND_PORT})\n219: \n220: echo \"Backend (port ${BACKEND_PORT}): ${BACKEND_OK}\"\n221: echo \"Frontend (port ${FRONTEND_PORT}): ${FRONTEND_OK}\"\n222: \n223: if [ \"$BACKEND_OK\" != \"000\" ] && [ \"$FRONTEND_OK\" = \"200\" ]; then\n224:   echo \"READY: All servers running\"\n225: else\n226:   echo \"FAIL: Server startup failed\"\n227:   pm2 logs ${PREFIX}-backend --lines 20\n228:   pm2 logs ${PREFIX}-frontend --lines 20\n229:   exit 1\n230: fi\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: ## Output\n236: \n237: On success, this skill produces:\n238: \n239: ```\n240: SERVERS_READY=true\n241: PREFIX={prefix}\n242: BACKEND_PORT={port}\n243: FRONTEND_PORT={port}\n244: BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:{port}/api\n245: FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:{port}\n246: ```\n247: \n248: These values should be used by downstream skills (smoke-test, playwright-qa-agent, etc.) instead of hardcoded URLs.\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ## Port Registry (Known Projects)\n253: \n254: Each project uses a unique preferred port range to allow simultaneous development:\n255: \n256: | Project | PREFIX | Backend | Frontend | Dashboards |\n257: |---------|--------|---------|----------|------------|\n258: | hire-agent | `ah` | 3000 | 5173 | 5174+ |\n259: | tirebank | `tb` | 3003 | 5175 | 5176+ |\n260: \n261: If a preferred port is occupied by another project, the skill auto-increments to find a free one.\n262: \n263: When adding new projects, assign the next available range:\n264: - Backend: next available 3xxx port\n265: - Frontend: next available 517x port\n266: \n267: ---\n268: \n269: ## Error Handling\n270: \n271: | Error | Action |\n272: |-------|--------|\n273: | Port occupied by another project | Auto-resolve: find next free port via `find_free_port` |\n274: | Port occupied by same project | `pm2 delete ${PREFIX}-*` then restart |\n275: | PM2 not installed | Fall back to `npm run start:dev &` |\n276: | Backend crashes on startup | Check `pm2 logs ${PREFIX}-backend --lines 50` for DB connection errors |\n277: | Frontend crashes on startup | Check `pm2 logs ${PREFIX}-frontend --lines 50` for build errors |\n278: | Health check timeout after 5 attempts | FAIL — report the issue, do not proceed |\n279: | `.env.local` port mismatch | Auto-fix and restart frontend |\n280: \n281: ---\n282: \n283: ## Integration with Other Skills\n284: \n285: This skill is a **prerequisite** for:\n286: - `smoke-test` — must run ensure-servers first\n287: - `playwright-qa-agent` — needs servers running\n288: - `e2e-test-generator` — needs servers for Playwright tests\n289: - Phase 8 (test-api) — Step 1 (smoke test)\n290: - Phase 9 (test-browser) — Steps 9b, 9c, 9d\n\n(End of file - total 290 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Ensures dev servers (backend + frontend) are running on the correct ports with health verification. Kills only this project's stale processes (via PM2 PREFIX), auto-resolves port collisions, and starts fresh. Supports multiple projects running simultaneously.\n---\n\n# Ensure Servers Skill\n\nDeterministic server startup protocol. Reads ports and PM2 prefix from project config, auto-resolves port collisions with other projects, kills only this project's stale processes, starts servers via PM2, and health-checks before returning.\n\n**Purpose**: Eliminate the class of bugs where QA/tests fail because servers aren't running, are on wrong ports, or another project occupies the port.\n\n**Multi-project safe**: Uses PM2 PREFIX from `ecosystem.config.js` to only manage this project's processes. If preferred ports are occupied by another project, auto-resolves to free ports.\n\n---\n\n## When to Use\n\nCall this skill BEFORE any phase that needs running servers:\n- Phase 8 (test-api) — smoke tests, backend API tests\n- Phase 9 (test-browser) — all sub-phases\n- `fullstack --phase test-browser` — smoke, acceptance","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/skills/dev/ensure-servers/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1779254733996,"end":1779254734275}},"id":"prt_e43d8a649001TMRwbvcrxzfnY4","sessionID":"ses_1bc27ca67ffe7twbk28GWfzUrI","messageID":"msg_e43d89617001yx9RJ73wpJlDXm"}}
